Poverty and lack of sex education among teenagers in Homabay county is being blamed for the increase in the number of teen pregnancies in the county. Matters have been made worse by some cultural practices that fuel the high number of teenage moms as HIV infections among adolescents is also on the rise. And as our reporter Beldeen Waliaula reports, many young girls are dropping out of schools while some of them have been forced into early marriages.
